column40: A TechStars Boston Alum, who's previously raised over 1MM. His background is in webhosting and Information Security, having founded ProHosters at age 17 (acquired by Carpathia Hosting in 2004), worked at ITA Software (acquired by Google in 2010) and Boston-based Veracode. He has a Bachelors of Science in Applied Networking Systems Administration from Rochester Institute of Technology, and a Masters in Engineering Management from Tufts University.
